The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Geometric to split stock

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, April 11: Geometric Software Solutions Ltd will sub-divide its stock to make its shares more affordable for the retail investor.

 The board of directors will meet on April 14 to consider the sub-division of shares, Geometric Software today informed the stock exchanges.

 On the Bombay Stock Exchange today, the shares of Geometric Software ended at Rs 493.90 after it had opened at Rs 405 and rose to an intra-day high of Rs 505.

 The company has entered into an agreement with OnCourse Technologies Inc to acquire TekSoft Inc and Cimtronics Inc for a total cash consideration of $1.75 million. 




